        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "T001 claims to satisfy the `<layer>-types.json` schema migration, but narrows the catalogue migration to `domain-types.json` and `infrastructure-types.json` only. That conflicts with `spec.json` IN-02/CN-04, which require a schema-version update and an explicit migration policy for the layer catalogues as a breaking change; the scoped `usecase-types.json` remains a layer catalogue and is left out of the planned migration. Implementing this as written can land the v4 codec while a scoped catalogue is still planned to stay at schema v3.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/spec-ref-embedded-hash-removal-2026-06-11/impl-plan.json",
              "line": 6,
              "category": "contradiction"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:53958c260d8e243789f4b9d3025305e756f643c700db473e4851bb1712c48e4a",
          "at": "2026-06-11T11:46:55Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "T001 is marked as covering IN-05/AC-07/AC-11, but its implementation scope only removes SpecRef hash fields from the type/codec/verifier paths and updates those verifier fixtures; it never includes the Chain② pair source or a ref-verify/cache-staleness verification. As written, an implementer can complete T001 while leaving the plan's promised behavior unverified: pair_source_chain2 must continue producing claim_hash from the hash-free catalogue-entry JSON, and a spec edit must stale the verify-cache without any spec_refs[].hash transcription. Add that code/test coverage to T001 or stop mapping those criteria to it.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/spec-ref-embedded-hash-removal-2026-06-11/impl-plan.json",
              "line": 6,
              "category": "contradiction"
            },
            {
              "message": "The spec requires the schema-breaking migration policy to be explicit for existing catalogues, either by migrating existing in-flight tracks or by declaring the break as new-catalogue-only, but T001 only says to migrate this track's own catalogue files to schema_version 4. That leaves the in-scope schema-version change without the required migration stance, so the task coverage for IN-02 is overstated.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/spec-ref-embedded-hash-removal-2026-06-11/impl-plan.json",
              "line": 6,
              "category": "contradiction"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:f97595e00ccc4aa2f1d427bbde565412c513265f3326f813feb800bf7212f32e",
          "at": "2026-06-11T11:52:57Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "CN-02 says SpecRef anchors must exist in `spec.json`'s `decisions[].id`, but SpecRef points at spec elements such as GO/IN/CN/AC IDs; `decisions[].id` is the ADR-frontmatter shape. This contradicts AC-03/AC-05/AC-06's requirement to validate anchors against actual spec elements and can send the implementation toward checking the wrong namespace for dangling anchors.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/spec-ref-embedded-hash-removal-2026-06-11/spec.json",
              "line": 204,
              "category": "factual error (semantic)"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:12658ef5bd22ca68356d6b4dfb9ae843035dc3f31ba6d5412a1d60c1ea0af98e",
          "at": "2026-06-11T11:57:47Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "IN-08 requires the catalogue codec plan to explicitly define how hash-containing old schema inputs are handled, choosing either error or ignore, but T001 is the only mapped task and only says to remove hash from the DTO/codec, bump SCHEMA_VERSION, migrate existing catalogues, and update tests. An implementation can complete T001 exactly as written while leaving the required old-schema behavior undefined, so the IN-08 coverage claim is semantically incomplete.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/spec-ref-embedded-hash-removal-2026-06-11/impl-plan.json",
